data.title: Above and Beyond!
data.text:
Hands down, one of the best meals that I have had this year!  Other posts described this place as noisy but despite a full room, it was not loud at all, maybe we had a good group of  well-behaved people the night I went.  Another post described the décor as cheesy….I say nay, nay. It was warm and inviting, a nice place to sit back, relax and enjoy a fine meal!
Service was friendly, efficient and informative. The bread they start you out with that comes with marinara and goat cheese was off the chain!  Bread is my Achilles and I was in major trouble!  The break was piping hot, perfectly crispy on the outside and delightfully chewy inside.  A bread lovers dream come true (mine’s as least!). I was a bit skeptical of the goat cheese and marinara but what a wonderful combination.  Goat cheese was creamy and light, marinara was not over powering or sweet.  
 We started out with the grilled long stem artichokes…simply divine! This is not your average artichoke dish.  I am sooo happy we decided to give it a try! So tender and flavorful….and the sauce it was served with?  I could have gotten a loaf of bread and sopped up a huge bowl of it and called it a night! I fought the urge to do so though!  
 
We ordered 3 fish dishes and they did not disappoint.  One was the special of the day, flounder over risotto topped with 2 large shrimp, the other was Mediterranean Sea Bass and the third was the Gulf Black Grouper.  All were nice sized portions and cooked to perfection. All were very tasty but the Grouper is what stood out to me.  I would order any of the three again. 
Dessert was the flourless chocolate cake with ice cream. While this was very good, it was not in my top 5. This is my husband’s favorite dessert….he did not have a problem finishing it.
While the prices may seem on the high side, I felt it was indicative of the value. This is a wonderful date night or special occasion restaurant for sure.  It is worth a visit if you are in the area and are wanting something special!

data.title: Seafood stew is delicious and filled with protein
data.text: The atmosphere is dressy, yet comfortable.  The food was delicious and not typical.  It was a perfect birthday dinner night.

data.title: Outstanding
data.text:
I went to the Johns Creek location so not sure if it's Duluth but here goes. 

We all really liked this place. The bread was the best I have had since moving south. They serve it with pomodoro and a huge scoop of ricotta cheese.  We ordered a few appetizers the Calamari, the mussels were all good. I had the sea bass which was fantastic. Very light nicely cooked. All in all everyone enjoyed their meal no complaints. I would also add that part of our party ran one half hour late.  The restaurant was accommodating and told us no stress the table was ours. Great experience. Would return although I do live in east cobb!

data.title: Dinner with friends
data.text: This was a first time visit for any of us and we're we pleased. No one was drinking alcohol but the service was exceptional. The waiter took very good care of us making suggestions as to what was his favorites. I had lasagna that was masterful. It was some of the best I have eaten. My wife told him what she liked and they put it together perfectly.  Our friends both had pork chops and we're really delighted.  Overall this restaurant deserves a revisit.

data.title: Best meal on our trip to Georgia
data.text:
We went for dinner with my brother-in-law and his wife.  It was without a doubt the best meal had during our trip.  The service was very good.  Ambiance is upscale, dimly lit and very elegant.  They do not allow children under the age of l4 except on Sundays.  This a great if you're looking for a nice evening out without children.

Bread with marinara sauce and goat cheese is brought to the table and it was really delicious.  Our table companions scoffed it down pretty quickly.  We ordered garganelli with homemade sausage in a tomato vodka sauce for the table and it was wonderful.  I'm glad we ordered it to share among 4 people as the serving was very generous and it would have been too much for 2 (that is generally what my husband and I do as he really likes pasta when we go for Italian food).  The entrees ordered were, Chicken parmigiana, Butternut squash ravioli, Veal chop and Lobster with linguine.  The portions were substantial and everyone was raving about their choice.  My lobster with linguine had a whole lobster tail on top of the order and there was also a fair bit of lobster mixed in with the linguine.

We were all too full for dessert.

data.title: Average food with lots of attitude
data.text: Went once with friends, food was good but not wow/amazing. Decided to try it again with my husband a few weeks later, on a Saturday night, and when we walked in the door we were seated immediately. When the waiter walked up he said, "I gotta get your whole order because the kitchen is about to close" -- what? Who wants to rush through ordering and then worry about the kitchen crew cleaning while making your meal? no thank you. We walked out and have never been back.

data.title: Great Veal Chop
data.text: Nice ambiance in this restaurant and curiously not as noisy as most US restaurants, I wonder if by the fact that they have lower lighting does this also reduce the volume people speak! Anyway, great food good service. I chose the veal chop that was cooked to perfection and several at our table chose the Veal Chop parmigiana which was huge but since it was so good they all polished them off, no doggy bags needed!

data.title: Excellent meal
data.text:
Italian food prepared as in Italy. Salsa via  appetizer and the octopus are amazing.
The cannelloni is also great.

data.title: Always our go to place with folks new to our area!
data.text: Excellent food and service. We asked for recommendations and the sausage appetizer was wonderful. Always a place to impress guests!

data.title: Huge Surprise
data.text: My wife and I went to Trattoria One 41 with some new friends for dinner.  It was our first visit but they had been before.  Actually it was the first time we knew about the restaurant.  The service was good, not great, but the food was excellent.  My wife ordered a salad and it never came.  When it was mentioned to the waiter he just said, "oh, ok, I am sorry".  Dinner was at the table by then, so no salad.  Our meals were great.  One of the best Italian dishes I have ever had.  We will definitely be back.

data.title: Fantastic Eggplant dish
data.text: Dinner last night was very nice. My husband had amazing chicken parmesan and I had the Eggplant dish. Both were great and so was the atmosphere.

data.title: My favorite Johns Creek restaurerant
data.text: I have eaten here many times and the food is consistently very good.  It can be a bit noisy but the pros far out way any cons.  A good dining experience.

data.title: Outstanding Italian Food
data.text: The Italian food is amazing, sauces are outstanding. great atmosphere especially in the Bar area. Staff is very knowledgeable & service is outstanding

data.title: Crazy mix of good and not-so-much!
data.text: The bread is awesome as is the marinara w goat cheese that they serve automatically. I ordered the eggplant involtini and was so disappointed that the sauce was super sweet, not at all like the marinara on the table. My husband had a clam and pasta dish and he said it was great.

data.title: Very Good!
data.text: This is a nice restaurant food is good!Service is great and they are very accommodating. Expensive for corking fees though.

data.title: nice visit interesting foods
data.text: We dined here a few weeks ago and it was a well made decision. Very Italian, Very good, My wife had pan seared scallops, very good, i had Osso Buco very tender. A little pricey but what isn't nowadays. It was well worth the trip and we only live a few minutes away so we will go back. Service was well done and everything was well worth it.

data.title: Excellent Local
data.text: This is always a great dinner - great for personal events or business dinners - a never go wrong place!

data.title: Great Ambiance, Service, and Food!
data.text:
When you walk into One41, its dimly lit creating a romantic atmosphere! 
One41 has been a place for several birthdays, dates, and girl's night out.

I highly recommend the Casarecce and Vongole. The sauce for these pasta dishes are more oil and wine based, which is more authentic then the cream and marinara based sauces found in your "everyday" Italian restaurants.
 
Also, the bread (appetizer) comes with a marinara mozzarella dipping sauce which is to die for! I highly recommend you to try it out! But make sure you make a reservation on the weekends because it can get a little busy.

data.title: The best Italian north of 285
data.text: Trattoria 141 has never disappointed me with their amazing Italian cuisine, friendly and knowledgeable servers, fine selection of wines and comfortable atmosphere.  I have dined here many times over the years and see no reason at all not to continue.  Simply the best.

data.title: Wow!
data.text: Received gift card for here.  Really impressed. Small place and a little noisy but excellent food and service. Two of us had pasta and two had scallops.  Also split a great flourless chocolate cake dessert. Need to try this place!!
